The Department of Small Business Development established five years ago will be welcoming the newly appointed Ministers who were sworn in yesterday. The new Minister together with the Deputy Minister is leading a critical ministry in the economic cluster tasked with the responsibility to empower and develop Small to Medium enterprises as well as Cooperatives. Minister Ntshavheni will be supported by a highly capable management team that seeks to ensure an enabling legislative and policy environment conducive for small businesses, cooperatives and the ever growing informal sector. The Department remains committed to its endeavour to radically transform the economy through the promotion and development of entrepreneurship whilst ensuring coordination, integration and mobilisation of resources and interventions for the sustainability and growth of SMMEs and Cooperatives in the country. Issued by: Department of Small Business Development